<L>__{exterior washington, d.c. street late afternoon}
<A>__{chance seems stumped on which way to go. he looks up one street, then the other, has no idea where they lead. he turns, looks behind him and sees a large statue of benito juarez pointing. chance smiles and goes off in the direction that benito points.}
<L>__{exterior rear of the white house dusk}
<A>__{tourists are gathered around gaping through the fence at the white house. chance is turned the other way, inspecting the branches of a dying tree. chance moves to a policeman standing nearby.}
<C>__{chance}
<D>__{excuse me...}
<P>__{(points to tree)}
<D>__{... that tree is very sick. it should be cared for.}
<A>__{the policeman looks at the tree, then at chance, figures a man dressed that well must be important.}
<C>__{policeman}
<D>__{yes sir. i will report it right away.}
<C>__{chance}
<D>__{yes. that would be a good thing to do. good day.}
<C>__{policeman}
<D>__{good day.}
<A>__{the policeman takes out his walkie talkie as chance walks away.}
